WEBVTT

00:02.685 --> 00:04.247
<font color="#00ff00">Meredith:</font> <i>When there's
a poisonous snake</i>

00:04.333 --> 00:06.435
<i>in our path,
we freeze</i>

00:07.026 --> 00:09.917
<font color="#ff8080">[ Breathing deeply ]</font>
<i>When we smell smoke, we run.</i>

00:10.134 --> 00:14.087
<i>When faced with danger,
fear takes over, and we react,</i>

00:14.279 --> 00:15.658
<i>desperate to feel safe.</i>

00:15.744 --> 00:16.767
<i>Jo!</i>

00:16.909 --> 00:18.666
You left
while I was in the shower.

00:18.873 --> 00:20.620
- What, are you avoiding me?
- Yes.

00:20.706 --> 00:22.267
Wait, not on purpose,
no.

00:22.353 --> 00:23.580
Sorry. Hi.
I just...

00:23.666 --> 00:25.588
<font color="#ff8080">[Inhales Deeply]</font> Bailey's back
to being chief tomorrow,

00:25.673 --> 00:27.401
so I have one last shot
at her full attention

00:27.486 --> 00:28.815
about a new grant
for my fellowship,

00:28.900 --> 00:30.854
and I just... I figured that
you would want to sleep in.

00:30.939 --> 00:32.744
- Yeah, but I was in the shower.
- Right.

00:32.876 --> 00:34.384
Jo, it's me.

00:34.603 --> 00:36.291
How long are we gonna
do this?

00:36.642 --> 00:38.401
Whatever happened with your
birth mom, you can tell me.

00:38.486 --> 00:39.666
Do you know
what the funding limits are

00:39.751 --> 00:41.728
on R90 or R15 grant?

00:41.874 --> 00:43.384
No. Jo...

00:43.470 --> 00:45.634
Okay, I got to figure that out
before Bailey gets here.

00:45.720 --> 00:46.720
I'm... sorry.

00:46.806 --> 00:49.393
- <font color="#00ff00">Meredith:</font> <i> It's biological... primal.
- <font color="#ff8080">[Sighs]</font></i>

00:50.949 --> 00:53.169
<i>But for someone
who suffers from trauma,</i>

00:53.831 --> 00:55.763
<i>it's the everyday things...</i>

00:56.155 --> 00:57.927
<i>a song in a coffee shop,</i>

00:58.083 --> 00:59.940
<i>the smell of rubbing alcohol..</i>

01:00.025 --> 01:01.003
<font color="#ff8080">[Bicycle bell dings]</font>

01:01.088 --> 01:04.215
<i>...seemingly random,
common things</i>

01:04.447 --> 01:07.474
<i>convincing your brain and body
you're in danger...</i>

01:07.608 --> 01:08.647
<font color="#ff8080">[Dog barks]</font>

01:08.834 --> 01:10.655
<i>...and there is no way out.</i>

01:12.712 --> 01:14.479
- <font color="#ff8080">[Doorbell Rings]</font>
- <font color="#ff8080">[Breathes deeply]</font>

01:17.564 --> 01:18.659
<font color="#ff8080">[Door creeaks lighly]</font>

01:18.744 --> 01:20.475
Hi.
What can I do for you?

01:23.247 --> 01:24.905
I'm Dr. Karev.

01:25.317 --> 01:27.006
Josephine. Jo.

01:27.092 --> 01:28.092
Um...

01:28.178 --> 01:29.811
<font color="#00ff00">Josh:</font> Mom,
I can't find my shoes!

01:29.897 --> 01:31.664
<font color="#00ff00">Alexandra:</font> <i>They're in the kitchen,
and they smell!</i>

01:31.749 --> 01:32.764
<i>Who ate all the cereal?</i>

01:32.850 --> 01:35.303
Honey, there's more
in the pantry. Y...

01:35.428 --> 01:36.991
<font color="#ff8080">[Dog barking]</font>

01:37.131 --> 01:40.139
Well, apparently, my kids forgot
that they were old enough

01:40.225 --> 01:42.577
to feed and
clothe themselves today.

01:42.697 --> 01:44.131
You have kids.

01:44.702 --> 01:48.288
Um, listen, if you're...
if you're selling magazines or...

01:48.373 --> 01:50.290
or religion,
we're good on both, so...

01:50.375 --> 01:51.444
But thank you so much.

01:51.530 --> 01:53.348
No, no. E-Emerson Hospital.

01:53.912 --> 01:55.294
Oh, right, okay.

01:55.381 --> 01:56.873
Well, if you just go here,

01:56.959 --> 01:58.123
- and you take Willowbrook...
- No, no, I-I was...

01:58.202 --> 02:00.682
- ...and then you're gonna...
- I was born at Emerson Hospital,

02:01.754 --> 02:05.811
and soon after, I was left at
the fire station on 47th Street.

02:05.968 --> 02:08.327
I think that you're the person
who left me.

02:10.650 --> 02:12.498
I think
you're my mother.

02:15.662 --> 02:18.053
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 15  Episode 19</font>

02:18.325 --> 02:20.998
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
Episode Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"Silent All These Years"</font>

02:21.959 --> 02:23.014
<font color="#ff8080">[Engine Rumbling]</font>

02:23.100 --> 02:24.358
<font color="#ff8080">[Horn honks]</font>

02:24.443 --> 02:26.280
You have
your chemistry report?

02:26.430 --> 02:28.040
- <font color="#ff8080">[Celephone clicking]</font>
- It's a paper, Mom.

02:28.125 --> 02:29.592
Yeah, as long as it's done,

02:29.678 --> 02:31.331
you can call it
whatever you like.

02:31.416 --> 02:34.092
Hey, um, I'm thinking about
Cal's Burgers tonight.

02:34.178 --> 02:35.546
Celebrate your
last day of sabbatical.

02:35.631 --> 02:36.811
- <font color="#ff8080">[Cellphone buttons clicking]</font>
- Can't.

02:36.896 --> 02:38.702
- I have a thing tonight.
- <font color="#ff8080">[Cellphone chimes]</font>

02:38.836 --> 02:40.053
With who?

02:40.497 --> 02:42.114
<font color="#ff8080">[Sighs]</font> With Kelly.

02:42.200 --> 02:43.857
- There's a Kelly?
- Define "thing."

02:43.943 --> 02:46.060
We're just talking,
is all.

02:46.669 --> 02:48.965
So, you can't come
have burgers with us,

02:49.168 --> 02:51.498
because you're talking to Kelly.

02:51.796 --> 02:53.904
- At a <i>thing.</i>
<i>- Here's fine.</i>

02:54.240 --> 02:55.454
<font color="#ff8080">[Horn honks]</font>

02:55.578 --> 02:57.521
We're nowhere near the school.
What?

02:57.643 --> 02:58.892
It's fine.

02:58.977 --> 03:00.561
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

03:00.646 --> 03:02.529
- Bye, love you!
- Good luck with your re...

03:02.614 --> 03:04.164
report!

03:04.249 --> 03:06.896
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

03:07.122 --> 03:08.572
It's a paper.

03:08.658 --> 03:10.025
I know.

03:12.755 --> 03:14.843
- Did he just put his arm around...
- He put his hand...

03:14.928 --> 03:16.576
<font color="#00ff00">Woman on P.A.:</font>
<i>Dr. Pannell to Plastics.</i>

03:16.685 --> 03:18.638
<i>Dr. Pannell to Plastics.</i>

03:18.755 --> 03:20.818
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

03:21.200 --> 03:22.516
<font color="#ff8080">[Teephone Elephone Ringingin distance]</font>

03:22.601 --> 03:24.795
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations Echoing]</font>

03:25.003 --> 03:26.912
<font color="#ff8080">[Echoing]</font> Oh, my God!
Sorry. Sorry.

03:27.087 --> 03:28.341
<font color="#ff8080">[Gasps]</font>

03:28.502 --> 03:30.524
Hey, you... you have a...
you have, um, a...

03:30.609 --> 03:32.178
<font color="#ff8080">[Normal voice]</font>
A-A crap sense of direction

03:32.263 --> 03:33.927
and can't find my way
to the ER.

03:34.177 --> 03:35.694
It's one floor down,
and then, if...

03:35.780 --> 03:37.697
<font color="#ff8080">[Teephone Elephone Ringingin distance]</font>

03:37.883 --> 03:39.755
You know,
why don't I take you?

03:41.186 --> 03:43.310
You ever have just a garbage
sort of day?

03:43.396 --> 03:44.638
<font color="#ff8080">[Scoffs]</font>

03:44.723 --> 03:46.412
More times than
I can count.

03:47.740 --> 03:49.130
This way.

03:49.395 --> 03:51.846
<font color="#ff8080">[Teephone Elephone Ringingin distance]</font>

03:52.064 --> 03:53.560
<font color="#ff8080">[Echoing]</font> You'll need stitches.

03:53.790 --> 03:56.135
I'll have a nurse bring you
a blanket.

03:56.727 --> 03:58.456
<font color="#ff8080">[Normal voice]</font> I feel so stupid.

03:59.558 --> 04:01.974
I was putting away dishes
and just...

04:02.091 --> 04:04.091
smacked myself in the face
with the cabinet.

04:04.177 --> 04:05.594
Such an idiot.

04:05.740 --> 04:06.944
<font color="#ff8080">[Echoing]</font> That cut looks
pretty deep,

04:07.029 --> 04:09.513
so Dr. Qadri will have to numb
it before we can clean it.

04:09.704 --> 04:11.240
When did this happen?

04:11.357 --> 04:12.763
<font color="#ff8080">[Normal voice]</font> Last night.

04:13.197 --> 04:15.466
I thought it would be fine,
but it just keeps bleeding.

04:15.552 --> 04:17.380
<font color="#ff8080">[Echoing]</font> Dr. Qadri
and I can help with that.

04:17.466 --> 04:19.546
I'm just gonna put a little
Betadine around the area,

04:19.992 --> 04:21.341
and you're just gonna feel
a little stick and a burn.

04:21.426 --> 04:22.749
Are you hurting anywhere else?

04:22.835 --> 04:24.687
<font color="#00ff00">Deluca:</font> Hey. Dr. Bailey's
been looking for you...

04:24.772 --> 04:26.835
- something about a grant deadline?
- Oh, okay.

04:26.921 --> 04:28.615
Um, I'm gonna be right...

04:28.700 --> 04:33.287
<font color="#ff8080">[Breathing quickly]</font>

04:33.372 --> 04:35.359
<font color="#ff8080">[Heartbeat pulsing]</font>

04:37.832 --> 04:40.695
<font color="#ff8080">[Normal voice]</font>
My patient here, Abby, she...

04:40.781 --> 04:43.406
hit her face on a cabinet.

04:43.762 --> 04:45.147
So if you could give us
some room, please,

04:45.232 --> 04:46.866
so I can suture her facial lac?

04:46.952 --> 04:49.077
And tell Dr. Bailey
that I will be a while.

04:49.581 --> 04:50.862
Thank you.

04:55.771 --> 04:57.365
Hey, why don't you sit up, okay?

04:57.906 --> 04:59.132
We'll sit you up. Okay.

04:59.581 --> 05:00.901
<font color="#ff8080">[Whimpers]</font>

05:01.274 --> 05:02.423
Is your belly hurting?

05:02.509 --> 05:04.859
No, it's just the cheek.

05:05.245 --> 05:07.968
You can fix it now, right?
So I can go.

05:08.354 --> 05:12.163
Dr. Qadri, um, can you go
get me some 4-0 MONOCRYL,

05:12.311 --> 05:14.429
and can we please
close those?

05:14.515 --> 05:15.562
Thank you.

05:15.647 --> 05:17.304
<font color="#ff8080">[Breathing deeply]</font>

05:22.788 --> 05:25.643
<font color="#ff8080">[Quietly]</font> Abby, it's just you and me.

05:26.758 --> 05:28.171
You're hurt.

05:28.405 --> 05:30.039
I am here to help.

05:32.497 --> 05:34.538
<font color="#ff8080">[Shuddering Breathing]</font>

05:36.616 --> 05:38.466
- Okay.
- <font color="#ff8080">[Whispering]</font> Okay.

05:38.770 --> 05:40.271
<font color="#ff8080">[Exhales sharply]</font>

05:41.859 --> 05:43.367
<font color="#ff8080">[Sniffles]</font>

05:54.319 --> 05:55.953
Okay. Okay.

05:57.789 --> 06:00.523
<font color="#ff8080">[Inhales sharply, whimpers]</font>

06:00.667 --> 06:03.913
<font color="#ff8080">[Breathing shakily]</font>

06:04.309 --> 06:05.734
I got you, Abby.

06:05.938 --> 06:08.070
I'm not going anywhere.

06:10.427 --> 06:12.378
<font color="#ff8080">[Breathing shakily]</font>

06:12.471 --> 06:14.663
<font color="#ff8080">[Door creaking]</font>

06:15.168 --> 06:17.018
<font color="#ff8080">[Breathing deeply]</font>

06:17.275 --> 06:18.859
<font color="#ff8080">[Quietly]</font> Look, I don't know
what you're after,

06:18.944 --> 06:19.893
but you can't be here.

06:19.978 --> 06:21.202
I'm not after anything.

06:21.288 --> 06:22.851
I just want to talk.

06:23.461 --> 06:25.178
You cannot be here.

06:25.302 --> 06:27.153
- <font color="#ff8080">[Dog barks]</font>
- <font color="#00ff00">Daniel:</font> Chip! <font color="#ff8080">[Claps hands]</font>

06:27.386 --> 06:29.406
Hey, Chip. Come here.

06:29.492 --> 06:30.737
Hey, buddy. <font color="#ff8080">[Chuckles]</font>

06:30.822 --> 06:33.307
I'll, uh, put him out back
and drop the kids at school.

06:33.392 --> 06:35.275
- <font color="#ff8080">[Chip Groans]</font>
- Is everything okay?

06:35.360 --> 06:36.711
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
I was just saying

06:36.796 --> 06:39.479
that we're already familiar
with the Book of Mormon, so...

06:39.601 --> 06:41.546
Ah, saw the original cast.
Loved it.

06:41.844 --> 06:44.929
Not a big fan of the book,
though, so... we're all set.

06:45.070 --> 06:46.335
<font color="#ff8080">[Chip barks]</font>

06:46.638 --> 06:48.639
<font color="#ff8080">[Birds chirping]</font>

06:53.178 --> 06:54.132
<font color="#ff8080">[Clears throat]</font>

06:54.218 --> 06:55.635
<font color="#ff8080">[Door closes]</font>

06:55.770 --> 06:58.929
There's a diner... a few miles up.

06:59.015 --> 07:00.398
Weird green roof?

07:00.484 --> 07:02.005
Ira's?

07:02.920 --> 07:04.523
One conversation.

07:04.955 --> 07:07.073
And you will never hear
from me again.

07:07.159 --> 07:11.468
<font color="#ffff00">[♪♪]</font>

07:11.641 --> 07:13.025
<font color="#ff8080">[Door creaking]</font>

07:13.165 --> 07:14.314
<font color="#ff8080">[Door slams shut]</font>

07:14.406 --> 07:16.441
<font color="#ffff00">[♪♪]</font>

07:20.762 --> 07:22.479
<font color="#ff8080">[Horn honking]</font>

07:22.894 --> 07:24.531
<font color="#ff8080">[Birds chirping]</font>

07:24.914 --> 07:26.973
<font color="#ff8080">[Liquid pouring]</font>

07:27.137 --> 07:28.387
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

07:28.489 --> 07:29.890
<font color="#ff8080">[Clock ticking]</font>

07:30.042 --> 07:31.199
<font color="#ff8080">[Bell jingles]</font>

07:31.339 --> 07:32.455
<font color="#ff8080">[Echoing]</font> Just one.

07:32.541 --> 07:33.981
<font color="#ff8080">[Echoing]</font> Oh, right this way.

07:34.097 --> 07:36.973
<font color="#ff8080">[Ticking clock echoes]</font>

07:37.059 --> 07:38.418
<font color="#ff8080">[Bell jingles]</font>

07:39.191 --> 07:40.716
<font color="#ff8080">[Ticking quickens]</font>

07:41.379 --> 07:42.614
<font color="#ff8080">[Silverware clatters lightly]</font>

07:42.746 --> 07:44.465
<font color="#ff8080">[Ticking quickens]</font>

07:44.551 --> 07:45.692
<font color="#ff8080">[Bell jingles]</font>

07:45.905 --> 07:47.496
<font color="#ff8080">[Ticking stops]</font>

07:48.754 --> 07:51.323
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

07:55.725 --> 07:57.887
<font color="#00ff00">MAN:</font> <i>Can I get you a warm-up?</i>

08:00.109 --> 08:02.660
<font color="#ff8080">[Conversations continue]</font>

08:03.056 --> 08:04.457
<font color="#ff8080">[Sighs]</font>

08:12.481 --> 08:14.278
The coffee here sucks.

08:14.364 --> 08:15.731
I've noticed.

08:17.150 --> 08:19.092
I'm late for work. Um...

08:22.622 --> 08:24.272
I work in the mayor's office.

08:24.357 --> 08:26.875
Try to create jobs
for under-served communities.

08:26.960 --> 08:29.878
<font color="#ff8080">[Dinnerware clattering lightly]</font>

08:30.083 --> 08:31.739
I'm sorry.
You knocked on my door.

08:31.825 --> 08:33.145
- I don't...
- You have a house...

08:33.255 --> 08:34.972
a really beautiful house.

08:35.058 --> 08:36.097
Thank you...?

08:36.183 --> 08:39.317
And kids and a husband
and a dog

08:39.403 --> 08:41.082
and crown frickin' moldings.

08:41.169 --> 08:42.440
Do you need money?
If this is about money...

08:42.525 --> 08:44.396
I don't need your damn money.

08:48.362 --> 08:49.842
Thank you.

08:50.608 --> 08:52.003
Look, I'm not quite sure

08:52.096 --> 08:53.285
- what you expected...
- In my head,

08:53.370 --> 08:55.917
you worked at
a diner half as nice as this.

08:56.650 --> 08:58.331
And you didn't graduate high school,

08:58.417 --> 09:00.057
or maybe you did
but a year or two late

09:00.143 --> 09:02.240
'cause they don't let pregnant
girls finish high school.

09:02.325 --> 09:04.979
And you scraped
by somehow on...

09:05.064 --> 09:06.995
hard work
and the kindness of strangers,

09:07.081 --> 09:08.283
but you had no one.

09:08.368 --> 09:09.815
You had nothing.

09:09.901 --> 09:12.159
That would make it okay
that I left you?

09:14.419 --> 09:17.371
I wanted you to have a better
life than I could give you...

09:17.456 --> 09:19.749
Now, <i>that</i> part
I heard in my head.

09:19.842 --> 09:21.319
I think it came

09:21.405 --> 09:23.569
- from a made-for-TV movie.
- No, I-I-I realized it

09:23.655 --> 09:26.330
the minute it came out
of my mouth, yes, um...

09:28.233 --> 09:29.700
But it's true.

09:31.341 --> 09:33.304
I really thought that
you'd be better off...

09:33.390 --> 09:34.514
What are their names?

09:34.600 --> 09:36.405
- I'm sorry?
- Your kids.

09:36.491 --> 09:39.788
My brother and sister eating
cereal in your perfect kitchen.

09:39.874 --> 09:41.179
What are their names?

09:41.265 --> 09:43.797
Alexandra is a senior in high school,

09:43.882 --> 09:46.585
and, uh, Josh is in 10th.

09:48.287 --> 09:52.231
And your husband, the,
what, the... accountant?

09:52.390 --> 09:53.702
Lawyer.

09:54.128 --> 09:55.654
Is he my father?

09:56.121 --> 09:57.332
No.

09:57.496 --> 09:59.847
No, he is nothing like... no.

09:59.932 --> 10:01.905
No, I met my husband in grad school.

10:01.991 --> 10:03.317
Um...

10:03.402 --> 10:04.492
His name is Daniel.

10:04.578 --> 10:05.734
Daniel.

10:06.725 --> 10:08.452
That's nice.

10:09.139 --> 10:10.499
That's really nice.

10:10.616 --> 10:13.093
You know,
I-I... I appreciate a girl

10:13.179 --> 10:14.187
with fire in her belly, but...

10:14.272 --> 10:16.450
I didn't have a better life.

10:17.271 --> 10:19.349
I wasn't better off.

10:20.551 --> 10:22.429
No one found me
adoring parents

10:22.515 --> 10:25.179
who were dying for a newborn
of their own to love.

10:25.265 --> 10:27.358
I lived in foster homes
so bad,

10:27.444 --> 10:29.850
it was better
to live in my car.

10:30.030 --> 10:32.452
And when a man finally told me
that he loved me,

10:32.538 --> 10:34.201
I believed him,

10:35.379 --> 10:39.293
even when he beat the crap out
of me so bad I couldn't see.

10:40.116 --> 10:42.457
So whatever life you had,

10:42.694 --> 10:45.621
tell me it wasn't better
than mine.

10:45.864 --> 10:48.479
<font color="#ff8080">[Indistinct conversations]</font>

10:51.647 --> 10:52.965
I should go.

10:53.051 --> 10:55.286
At least you're consistent.
<font color="#ff8080">[Clears throat]</font>

10:55.821 --> 10:57.822
<font color="#ff8080">[Breathing deeply]</font>

11:01.647 --> 11:03.819
Did you honestly come here
to punish me?

11:03.905 --> 11:04.796
Consider it done.

11:04.882 --> 11:06.906
I came because I don't know
anything about where I'm from,

11:06.991 --> 11:08.882
and I want to know.

11:10.902 --> 11:13.804
<font color="#ff8080">[Dinnerware clinking]</font>

11:19.344 --> 11:20.933
Um...

11:21.585 --> 11:23.394
My, um...

11:24.749 --> 11:26.296
father's side is pure Irish.

11:26.382 --> 11:29.147
My... My... My mother
is Russian Jew and Italian.

11:29.233 --> 11:31.038
I got all that
from spitting in a tube.

11:31.140 --> 11:32.788
My mother's parents...

11:33.143 --> 11:34.561
died when she was young...

11:34.647 --> 11:36.147
heart disease and cancer.

11:36.233 --> 11:37.811
So I'm afraid that's
in the mix.

11:38.233 --> 11:41.280
Uh, there's no history of
mental illness that I'm aware...

11:41.366 --> 11:44.202
- That's not what I'm asking.
- Then what do you want to know?

11:44.288 --> 11:46.397
Something I can't get
from spitting in a tube!

11:47.882 --> 11:49.156
Ah.

11:49.483 --> 11:52.725
I, um...
I grew up on a farm in Kansas.

